ℹ Mid is 1-indexed in VB; VBR shifts the position for you and counts by characters (not bytes), so it stays correct on any text — Mid(s, 2, 3) is s.chars().skip(1).take(3).
ℹ InStr becomes Rust's .find(), which returns an Option: Some(pos) when found, None when not. You handle both instead of checking for 0.
ℹ Val becomes Rust's .parse(), which returns a Result: parsing can fail, so you handle the error rather than getting a silent 0.